result.name: Crossing Boat Restaurant

reviews.text: No casualties , this place is a bestseller and once you eat here, it would only make sense.  None pretentious atmosphere just spices up the experience to give it more authentic flare. Anything from the menu here makes this restaurant enjoyable share-house full with warm memories for time spent in joy. Try the fishball soup and the noodles and eat like a local. Honestly, I would have never visited this place if it was not for my father in law who knows the area well enough. So glad to have him to be my personal tour-guide ... Still wonder if you should visit, well you can try me  @travelogion

Good food at reasonable price, perfect after a hike. Try to get a table on the riverside rather than upstairs above the kitchen, can get extremely smelly from all the frying and will definitely stink out your clothes.

Overpriced tourist trap. Squid was tough as boots, not chewable and overcooked, and waiter service hiding nowhere to be seen, eventually did not even offer to replace or refund, only cut up into smaller pieces. Additional 10% service charge but did not see it mentioned in the menu, and what service - paid for hiding? Total for 4 dishes shown (mostly vegetables) was expensive $530 HKD. Poor food quality. There are much better and busier places within walking distance of the fishing village with better food and service.
Nice range of dishes in the center of the village. The dishes with shrimp paste are best.

The snobbish waiter hardsell the expensive food to foreign tourists and local tourists. I had a experience here, I saw the foreigners had only ordered the fried rice and drink(two persons sit down),the old waiter ,who wears with glasses, held up two of his fingers and did not satisfy the tourist’s order, speak loudly,  “only two things......sssssss.Afterwards, when tourist would like to ask for the position of toilet ,he misunderstood or laughed at him, do you want to order more things.....ssss.   Poor food ,poor service, I promise myself never go there . The money is not important, I am so disappointed how this fk restaurant behalf  of the hk food for tourists in countryside ?
